# TURN relay — REQUIRED for reliable play across different networks.
#
# WebRTC needs a TURN relay when peers are behind symmetric NATs / strict
# firewalls (~1/3 of connections, and common on mobile/corporate networks).
# Free no-signup public TURN is no longer reliable, so configure one of the
# options below. Both free tiers below take ~2 minutes to set up.
#
# All Vite env vars exposed to the client MUST be prefixed with VITE_.
# After editing, restart `npm run dev`.

# ---- Option A (easiest): a REST endpoint that returns a ready iceServers array.
# Metered: create a free app at https://dashboard.metered.ca (50 GB/mo free),
# then copy your "TURN Credentials API" URL. It looks like:
#   https://<yourapp>.metered.live/api/v1/turn/credentials?apiKey=xxxxxxxx
VITE_TURN_API_URL=

# ---- Option B: static TURN credentials (e.g. ExpressTURN free 1000 GB/mo,
# https://www.expressturn.com). Comma-separate multiple urls; include :443 and
# a ?transport=tcp variant for firewall-restricted networks.
VITE_TURN_URLS=
VITE_TURN_USERNAME=
VITE_TURN_CREDENTIAL=
